Ahnu Nahki wrote:

&gt;Is there a way to only have heritrix downloaded all text/html markup
&gt;and disregard altogether images and other binaries. I notice that this
&gt;eats up alot of time on our crawls.
&gt;
&gt;Thanks,
&gt;Ahnu
&gt;  
&gt;

This topic has been discussed variously here on the list.  You might 
check the archive.

In short, not without doing some work.  Lesser work would be a filter 
that skipped non-text/html content after download.  More work would be a 
check that interrupted crawls mid-download if the type was other than 
what you wanted. 

Though sub-optimal, you could try and write a regex that only excludes 
resources with URIs that match a particular pattern.

